{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2206,"text":"I'm a potter,"},{"time":5224,"text":"which seems like a fairly humble vocation."},{"time":9749,"text":"I know a lot about pots."},{"time":12629,"text":"I've spent about 15 years making them."},{"time":16309,"text":"One of the things that really\nexcites me in my artistic practice"},{"time":19339,"text":"and being trained as a potter"},{"time":22056,"text":"is that you very quickly learn\nhow to make great things out of nothing;"},{"time":27500,"text":"that I spent a lot of time at my wheel\nwith mounds of clay trying stuff;"},{"time":34283,"text":"and that the limitations\nof my capacity, my ability,"},{"time":37775,"text":"was based on my hands and my imagination;"},{"time":40506,"text":"that if I wanted to make\na really nice bowl"},{"time":42706,"text":"and I didn't know how to make a foot yet,"},{"time":44810,"text":"I would have to learn how to make a foot;"},{"time":47829,"text":"that that process of learning\nhas been very, very helpful to my life."},{"time":52983,"text":"I feel like, as a potter,"},{"time":54957,"text":"you also start to learn\nhow to shape the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59067,"text":"There have been times\nin my artistic capacity"},{"time":62178,"text":"that I wanted to reflect"},{"time":65041,"text":"on other really important moments"},{"time":67704,"text":"in the history of the U.S.,\nthe history of the world"},{"time":71814,"text":"where tough things happened,"},{"time":73405,"text":"but how do you talk about tough ideas"},{"time":76086,"text":"without separating people\nfrom that content?"},{"time":80196,"text":"Could I use art like these old,\ndiscontinued firehoses from Alabama,"},{"time":85792,"text":"to talk about the complexities of a moment\nof civil rights in the '60s?"},{"time":91946,"text":"Is it possible to talk about my father\nand I doing labor projects?"},{"time":96797,"text":"My dad was a roofer, construction guy,\nhe owned small businesses,"},{"time":100954,"text":"and at 80, he was ready to retire\nand his tar kettle was my inheritance."},{"time":107850,"text":"Now, a tar kettle doesn't sound\nlike much of an inheritance. It wasn't."},{"time":111659,"text":"It was stinky and it took up\na lot of space in my studio,"},{"time":115606,"text":"but I asked my dad if he would be willing\nto make some art with me,"},{"time":119901,"text":"if we could reimagine this kind\nof nothing material"},{"time":123732,"text":"as something very special."},{"time":126217,"text":"And by elevating the material\nand my dad's skill,"},{"time":129607,"text":"could we start to think about tar\njust like clay, in a new way,"},{"time":135905,"text":"shaping it differently,\nhelping us to imagine what was possible?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":141607,"text":"After clay, I was then kind of turned on\nto lots of different kinds of materials,"},{"time":145790,"text":"and my studio grew a lot\nbecause I thought, well,"},{"time":148762,"text":"it's not really about the material,\nit's about our capacity to shape things."},{"time":152849,"text":"I became more and more interested in ideas"},{"time":155705,"text":"and more and more things that \nwere happening just outside my studio."},{"time":161897,"text":"Just to give you a little bit of context,\nI live in Chicago."},{"time":165104,"text":"I live on the South Side now.\nI'm a West Sider."},{"time":168359,"text":"For those of you who are not Chicagoans,\nthat won't mean anything,"},{"time":171773,"text":"but if I didn't mention\nthat I was a West Sider,"},{"time":174025,"text":"there would be a lot of people\nin the city that would be very upset."}]},{"cues":[{"time":178204,"text":"The neighborhood that I live in\nis Grand Crossing."},{"time":181153,"text":"It's a neighborhood\nthat has seen better days."},{"time":184976,"text":"It is not a gated community by far."},{"time":189071,"text":"There is lots of abandonment\nin my neighborhood,"},{"time":192205,"text":"and while I was kind of busy\nmaking pots and busy making art"},{"time":195711,"text":"and having a good art career,"},{"time":197662,"text":"there was all of this stuff\nthat was happening"},{"time":199807,"text":"just outside my studio."},{"time":202460,"text":"All of us know about\nfailing housing markets"},{"time":205748,"text":"and the challenges of blight,"},{"time":207580,"text":"and I feel like we talk about it\nwith some of our cities more than others,"},{"time":211057,"text":"but I think a lot of our\nU.S. cities and beyond"},{"time":213991,"text":"have the challenge of blight,"},{"time":216011,"text":"abandoned buildings that people\nno longer know what to do anything with."},{"time":220237,"text":"And so I thought, is there a way\nthat I could start to think"},{"time":223093,"text":"about these buildings as an extension\nor an expansion of my artistic practice?"},{"time":228479,"text":"And that if I was thinking\nalong with other creatives --"},{"time":231498,"text":"architects, engineers,\nreal estate finance people --"},{"time":235166,"text":"that us together might be able\nto kind of think"},{"time":238046,"text":"in more complicated ways\nabout the reshaping of cities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243085,"text":"And so I bought a building."},{"time":244733,"text":"The building was really affordable."},{"time":247473,"text":"We tricked it out."},{"time":249185,"text":"We made it as beautiful as we could\nto try to just get some activity happening"},{"time":253620,"text":"on my block."},{"time":255872,"text":"Once I bought the building\nfor about 18,000 dollars,"},{"time":258310,"text":"I didn't have any money left."},{"time":260330,"text":"So I started sweeping the building\nas a kind of performance."},{"time":265599,"text":"This is performance art,\nand people would come over,"},{"time":268341,"text":"and I would start sweeping."},{"time":269897,"text":"Because the broom was free\nand sweeping was free."},{"time":272544,"text":"It worked out."},{"time":274703,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":276938,"text":"But we would use the building, then,\nto stage exhibitions, small dinners,"},{"time":282389,"text":"and we found that that building\non my block, Dorchester --"},{"time":286336,"text":"we now referred to the block\nas Dorchester projects --"},{"time":289052,"text":"that in a way that building\nbecame a kind of gathering site"},{"time":292535,"text":"for lots of different kinds of activity."},{"time":294769,"text":"We turned the building into\nwhat we called now the Archive House."},{"time":299222,"text":"The Archive House would do\nall of these amazing things."},{"time":302403,"text":"Very significant people\nin the city and beyond"},{"time":305747,"text":"would find themselves\nin the middle of the hood."},{"time":308422,"text":"And that's when I felt like"},{"time":310790,"text":"maybe there was a relationship\nbetween my history with clay"},{"time":313602,"text":"and this new thing that was\nstarting to develop,"},{"time":316172,"text":"that we were slowly starting"},{"time":318514,"text":"to reshape how people imagined\nthe South Side of the city."}]},{"cues":[{"time":323440,"text":"One house turned into a few houses,"},{"time":325622,"text":"and we always tried to suggest"},{"time":328084,"text":"that not only is creating\na beautiful vessel important,"},{"time":332008,"text":"but the contents of what happens\nin those buildings is also very important."},{"time":335884,"text":"So we were not only thinking\nabout development,"},{"time":338532,"text":"but we were thinking about the program,"},{"time":340854,"text":"thinking about the kind of connections\nthat could happen"},{"time":344360,"text":"between one house and another,\nbetween one neighbor and another."},{"time":350159,"text":"This building became what we call\nthe Listening House,"},{"time":353181,"text":"and it has a collection of discarded books"},{"time":356431,"text":"from the Johnson Publishing Corporation,"},{"time":359102,"text":"and other books from an old bookstore\nthat was going out of business."},{"time":363095,"text":"I was actually just wanting to activate\nthese buildings as much as I could"},{"time":367368,"text":"with whatever and whoever would join me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":371678,"text":"In Chicago, there's\namazing building stock."},{"time":374612,"text":"This building, which had been\nthe former crack house on the block,"},{"time":378791,"text":"and when the building became abandoned,"},{"time":381345,"text":"it became a great opportunity to really\nimagine what else could happen there."},{"time":385246,"text":"So this space we converted into\nwhat we call Black Cinema House."},{"time":389298,"text":"Black Cinema House was an opportunity\nin the hood to screen films"},{"time":393419,"text":"that were important and relevant\nto the folk who lived around me,"},{"time":397633,"text":"that if we wanted to show\nan old Melvin Van Peebles film, we could."},{"time":401348,"text":"If we wanted to show \"Car Wash,\" we could."},{"time":404018,"text":"That would be awesome."},{"time":405991,"text":"The building we soon outgrew,"},{"time":408546,"text":"and we had to move to a larger space."},{"time":411053,"text":"Black Cinema House, which was made\nfrom just a small piece of clay,"},{"time":415488,"text":"had to grow into a much larger\npiece of clay, which is now my studio."}]},{"cues":[{"time":422779,"text":"What I realized was that\nfor those of you who are zoning junkies,"},{"time":426588,"text":"that some of the things that I was doing"},{"time":428582,"text":"in these buildings\nthat had been left behind,"},{"time":431881,"text":"they were not the uses by which\nthe buildings were built,"},{"time":435713,"text":"and that there are city policies that say,"},{"time":437941,"text":"\"Hey, a house that is residential\nneeds to stay residential.\""},{"time":441260,"text":"But what do you do in neighborhoods when\nain't nobody interested in living there?"},{"time":446067,"text":"That the people who have\nthe means to leave have already left?"},{"time":450011,"text":"What do we do with\nthese abandoned buildings?"},{"time":452498,"text":"And so I was trying\nto wake them up using culture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455703,"text":"We found that that\nwas so exciting for folk,"},{"time":458706,"text":"and people were so responsive to the work,\nthat we had to then find bigger buildings."},{"time":463271,"text":"By the time we found bigger buildings,"},{"time":465316,"text":"there was, in part, the resources \nnecessary to think about those things."},{"time":469569,"text":"In this bank that we called the Arts Bank,\nit was in pretty bad shape."},{"time":473901,"text":"There was about six feet\nof standing water."},{"time":477187,"text":"It was a difficult project to finance,"},{"time":479649,"text":"because banks weren't interested\nin the neighborhood"},{"time":482079,"text":"because people weren't interested\nin the neighborhood"},{"time":484641,"text":"because nothing had happened there."},{"time":486742,"text":"It was dirt. It was nothing.\nIt was nowhere."},{"time":490724,"text":"And so we just started imagining,\nwhat else could happen in this building?"},{"time":496381,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":501846,"text":"And so now that the rumor\nof my block has spread,"},{"time":504615,"text":"and lots of people are starting to visit,"},{"time":506595,"text":"we've found that the bank\ncan now be a center"},{"time":508696,"text":"for exhibition, archives,\nmusic performance,"},{"time":511908,"text":"and that there are people\nwho are now interested"},{"time":514686,"text":"in being adjacent to those buildings\nbecause we brought some heat,"},{"time":518224,"text":"that we kind of made a fire."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520677,"text":"One of the archives that we'll have there\nis this Johnson Publishing Corporation."},{"time":524926,"text":"We've also started to collect\nmemorabilia from American history,"},{"time":528525,"text":"from people who live\nor have lived in that neighborhood."},{"time":532356,"text":"Some of these images\nare degraded images of black people,"},{"time":536094,"text":"kind of histories\nof very challenging content,"},{"time":539368,"text":"and where better than a neighborhood"},{"time":541829,"text":"with young people who are constantly\nasking themselves about their identity"},{"time":546099,"text":"to talk about some of the complexities"},{"time":548354,"text":"of race and class?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":550896,"text":"In some ways, the bank represents a hub,"},{"time":554623,"text":"that we're trying to create a pretty \nhardcore node of cultural activity,"},{"time":559975,"text":"and that if we could start\nto make multiple hubs"},{"time":562842,"text":"and connect some cool\ngreen stuff around there,"},{"time":565791,"text":"that the buildings that we've\npurchased and rehabbed,"},{"time":568740,"text":"which is now around 60 or 70 units,"},{"time":572014,"text":"that if we could land\nminiature Versailles on top of that,"},{"time":577447,"text":"and connect these buildings\nby a beautiful greenbelt --"},{"time":580930,"text":"(Applause) --"},{"time":583855,"text":"that this place where people\nnever wanted to be"},{"time":587315,"text":"would become an important destination"},{"time":589776,"text":"for folk from all over\nthe country and world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":593027,"text":"In some ways, it feels\nvery much like I'm a potter,"},{"time":596812,"text":"that we tackle the things\nthat are at our wheel,"},{"time":600225,"text":"we try with the skill that we have"},{"time":602488,"text":"to think about this next bowl\nthat I want to make."},{"time":607028,"text":"And it went from a bowl to a singular\nhouse to a block to a neighborhood"},{"time":611927,"text":"to a cultural district\nto thinking about the city,"},{"time":614621,"text":"and at every point, there were things\nthat I didn't know that I had to learn."},{"time":618707,"text":"I've never learned so much\nabout zoning law in my life."},{"time":621749,"text":"I never thought I'd have to."},{"time":623529,"text":"But as a result of that, I'm finding\nthat there's not just room"},{"time":626486,"text":"for my own artistic practice,"},{"time":628227,"text":"there's room for a lot of other\nartistic practices."}]},{"cues":[{"time":631803,"text":"So people started asking us,"},{"time":633382,"text":"\"Well, Theaster, how are you\ngoing to go to scale?\""},{"time":635853,"text":"and, \"What's your sustainability plan?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":637988,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":642739,"text":"And what I found was that\nI couldn't export myself,"},{"time":646616,"text":"that what seems necessary\nin cities like Akron, Ohio,"},{"time":650355,"text":"and Detroit, Michigan, and Gary, Indiana,"},{"time":652955,"text":"is that there are people in those places\nwho already believe in those places,"},{"time":656653,"text":"that are already dying\nto make those places beautiful,"},{"time":659579,"text":"and that often, those people\nwho are passionate about a place"},{"time":663038,"text":"are disconnected from the resources\nnecessary to make cool things happen,"},{"time":667450,"text":"or disconnected from\na contingency of people"},{"time":670027,"text":"that could help make things happen."},{"time":671908,"text":"So now, we're starting to give advice\naround the country"},{"time":676200,"text":"on how to start with what you got,"},{"time":678345,"text":"how to start with the things\nthat are in front of you,"},{"time":681140,"text":"how to make something out of nothing,"},{"time":683517,"text":"how to reshape your world\nat a wheel or at your block"},{"time":688045,"text":"or at the scale of the city."}]},{"cues":[{"time":690530,"text":"Thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":692225,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":699695,"text":"June Cohen: Thank you. So I think\nmany people watching this"},{"time":703201,"text":"will be asking themselves\nthe question you just raised at the end:"},{"time":706406,"text":"How can they do this in their own city?"},{"time":708588,"text":"You can't export yourself."},{"time":710209,"text":"Give us a few pages out of your playbook\nabout what someone who is inspired"},{"time":713882,"text":"about their city can do\nto take on projects like yours?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":716772,"text":"Theaster Gates: One of the things\nI've found that's really important"},{"time":719965,"text":"is giving thought to not just\nthe kind of individual project,"},{"time":724052,"text":"like an old house,"},{"time":726846,"text":"but what's the relationship\nbetween an old house,"},{"time":729717,"text":"a local school, a small bodega,"},{"time":732875,"text":"and is there some kind of synergy\nbetween those things?"},{"time":735871,"text":"Can you get those folk talking?"},{"time":738169,"text":"I've found that in cases\nwhere neighborhoods have failed,"},{"time":742720,"text":"they still often have a pulse."},{"time":744903,"text":"How do you identify the pulse\nin that place, the passionate people,"},{"time":748362,"text":"and then how do you get folk\nwho have been fighting,"},{"time":751367,"text":"slogging for 20 years, reenergized\nabout the place that they live?"},{"time":755758,"text":"And so someone has to do that work."},{"time":758219,"text":"If I were a traditional developer,\nI would be talking about buildings alone,"},{"time":762492,"text":"and then putting\na \"For Lease\" sign in the window."},{"time":766439,"text":"I think that you actually\nhave to curate more than that,"},{"time":769086,"text":"that there's a way in which\nyou have to be mindful about,"},{"time":771784,"text":"what are the businesses\nthat I want to grow here?"},{"time":774840,"text":"And then, are there people\nwho live in this place"},{"time":777282,"text":"who want to grow those businesses with me?"},{"time":779302,"text":"Because I think it's not just\na cultural space or housing;"},{"time":782135,"text":"there has to be the recreation\nof an economic core."},{"time":785177,"text":"So thinking about those things\ntogether feels right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":788845,"text":"JC: It's hard to get people\nto create the spark again"},{"time":791651,"text":"when people have been\nslogging for 20 years."},{"time":793698,"text":"Are there any methods you've found\nthat have helped break through?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":796815,"text":"TG: Yeah, I think that now\nthere are lots of examples"},{"time":799782,"text":"of folk who are doing amazing work,"},{"time":801616,"text":"but those methods are sometimes like,\nwhen the media is constantly saying"},{"time":806051,"text":"that only violent things\nhappen in a place,"},{"time":809023,"text":"then based on your skill set\nand the particular context,"},{"time":812320,"text":"what are the things that you can do\nin your neighborhood"},{"time":815640,"text":"to kind of fight some of that?"},{"time":817765,"text":"So I've found that\nif you're a theater person,"},{"time":820668,"text":"you have outdoor street theater festivals."},{"time":822943,"text":"In some cases, we don't have\nthe resources in certain neighborhoods"},{"time":826867,"text":"to do things that are\na certain kind of splashy,"},{"time":830211,"text":"but if we can then find ways\nof making sure that people"},{"time":833322,"text":"who are local to a place,"},{"time":834854,"text":"plus people who could be supportive\nof the things that are happening locally,"},{"time":838686,"text":"when those people get together,"},{"time":840450,"text":"I think really amazing things can happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":842586,"text":"JC: So interesting."},{"time":844072,"text":"And how can you make sure\nthat the projects you're creating"},{"time":846394,"text":"are actually for the disadvantaged"},{"time":848159,"text":"and not just for the sort of\nvegetarian indie movie crowd"},{"time":852199,"text":"that might move in\nto take advantage of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":854318,"text":"TG: Right on. So I think this is where\nit starts to get into the thick weeds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":859359,"text":"JC: Let's go there.\nTG: Right now, Grand Crossing"},{"time":861996,"text":"is 99 percent black, or at least living,"},{"time":864993,"text":"and we know that maybe\nwho owns property in a place"},{"time":868313,"text":"is different from who walks\nthe streets every day."},{"time":870774,"text":"So it's reasonable to say\nthat Grand Crossing is already"},{"time":873630,"text":"in the process of being something\ndifferent than it is today."},{"time":877485,"text":"But are there ways to think about\nhousing trusts or land trusts"},{"time":883080,"text":"or a mission-based development"},{"time":885518,"text":"that starts to protect\nsome of the space that happens,"},{"time":888281,"text":"because when you have\n7,500 empty lots in a city,"},{"time":892600,"text":"you want something to happen there,"},{"time":894551,"text":"but you need entities that are not\njust interested in the development piece,"},{"time":899055,"text":"but entities that are interested\nin the stabilization piece,"},{"time":902143,"text":"and I feel like often the developer piece\nis really motivated,"},{"time":905649,"text":"but the other work of a kind\nof neighborhood consciousness,"},{"time":909016,"text":"that part doesn't live anymore."},{"time":910990,"text":"So how do you start to grow up\nimportant watchdogs"},{"time":915796,"text":"that ensure that the resources\nthat are made available"},{"time":918518,"text":"to new folk that are coming in"},{"time":919954,"text":"are also distributed to folk\nwho have lived in a place for a long time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":923346,"text":"JC: That makes so much sense.\nOne more question:"},{"time":925955,"text":"You make such a compelling case for beauty\nand the importance of beauty and the arts."},{"time":930002,"text":"There would be others who would argue\nthat funds would be better spent"},{"time":933280,"text":"on basic services for the disadvantaged."},{"time":936484,"text":"How do you combat that viewpoint,\nor come against it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":940194,"text":"TG: I believe that beauty \nis a basic service."},{"time":942694,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":950333,"text":"Often what I have found is that\nwhen there are resources"},{"time":954168,"text":"that have not been made available\nto certain under-resourced cities"},{"time":957628,"text":"or neighborhoods or communities,"},{"time":959694,"text":"that sometimes culture is the thing\nthat helps to ignite,"},{"time":964397,"text":"and that I can't do everything,"},{"time":967037,"text":"but I think that there's a way in which\nif you can start with culture"},{"time":970444,"text":"and get people kind of\nreinvested in their place,"},{"time":973416,"text":"other kinds of adjacent\namenities start to grow,"},{"time":977689,"text":"and then people can make a demand\nthat's a poetic demand,"},{"time":981642,"text":"and the political demands that\nare necessary to wake up our cities,"},{"time":986883,"text":"they also become very poetic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":988646,"text":"JC: It makes perfect sense to me."},{"time":990558,"text":"Theaster, thank you so much\nfor being here with us today."},{"time":993225,"text":"Thank you. Theaster Gates."}]},{"cues":[{"time":994476,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}